1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,160
Hello everyone and welcome to EnglishPod.
大家好，欢迎收听EnglishPod。

2
00:00:05,160 --> 00:00:06,160
My name is Marco.
我是Marco。

3
00:00:06,160 --> 00:00:10,720
My name is Catherine and today we're looking for a new job.
我是Catherine，今天我们正在找新工作。

4
00:00:10,720 --> 00:00:15,200
That's right, we are looking for a new job and so we're bringing you this great lesson
没错，我们正在找新工作，所以为大家带来了这节精彩的课程。

5
00:00:15,200 --> 00:00:19,520
where we're going to teach you in English a lot of terms related with looking for a
在这节课里，我们会教大家很多与找工作相关的英语词汇。

6
00:00:19,520 --> 00:00:22,760
job or things like a resume, cover letter.
比如简历、求职信之类的。

7
00:00:22,760 --> 00:00:27,260
So before we get into that, why don't we take a look at a word that we have in Vocabulary
在进入正题之前，我们先来看看词汇预览里的一个词。

8
00:00:27,260 --> 00:00:29,680
Preview.
词汇预览。

9
00:00:29,680 --> 00:00:31,440
Vocabulary Preview.
词汇预览。

10
00:00:31,440 --> 00:00:33,880
So this is actually the name of a job.
这其实是一个职位名称。

11
00:00:33,880 --> 00:00:34,880
It's a position.
它是一个岗位。

12
00:00:34,880 --> 00:00:37,320
It's a gas station attendant.
加油站服务员。

13
00:00:37,320 --> 00:00:40,100
Okay, a gas station attendant.
好的，加油站服务员。

14
00:00:40,100 --> 00:00:41,920
Now we know what a gas station is, right?
我们都知道加油站是什么，对吧？

15
00:00:41,920 --> 00:00:42,920
That's right.
没错。

16
00:00:42,920 --> 00:00:45,080
It's a place where you go to fill your car with gas.
就是你去给车加油的地方。

17
00:00:45,080 --> 00:00:46,080
Okay.
好的。

18
00:00:46,080 --> 00:00:48,880
So an attendant at a gas station, what does he do?
那么加油站的服务员是做什么的呢？

19
00:00:48,880 --> 00:00:53,320
He or she is a person who will help you put the gas in your car.
他或她会帮你给车加油。

20
00:00:53,320 --> 00:00:57,840
So an attendant is someone who is almost like an assistant or a helper.
所以服务员就像是助手或帮手一样的人。

21
00:00:57,840 --> 00:01:01,040
You can have a bathroom attendant, someone who gives you a towel after you wash your
你可以雇一个洗手间服务员，就是那种在你洗完手后递毛巾的人。

22
00:01:01,040 --> 00:01:02,040
hands.
手。

23
00:01:02,040 --> 00:01:03,040
I've seen those in the fancy restaurants.
我在高档餐厅见过那种。

24
00:01:03,040 --> 00:01:05,680
Yeah, so gas station attendant.
对，就像加油站服务员一样。

25
00:01:05,680 --> 00:01:09,520
Alright, so why don't we take a look now at our dialogue.
好了，那我们现在来看看对话吧。

26
00:01:09,520 --> 00:01:15,480
Let's listen to it for the first time and we'll be back in a bit.
我们第一次听一下，一会儿再回来。

27
00:01:15,480 --> 00:01:17,920
Woohoo!
哇哦！

28
00:01:17,920 --> 00:01:23,680
This just might be the start of the rest of my life.
这可能是我余生的开始。

29
00:01:23,680 --> 00:01:24,680
What happened?
发生什么事了？

30
00:01:24,680 --> 00:01:27,040
I'm in the market for a job.
我正在找工作。

31
00:01:27,040 --> 00:01:31,640
I went on a website with hundreds of job listings in the area and browsed through them until
我上了一个网站，上面有本地几百个职位列表，我浏览了一遍，直到

32
00:01:31,640 --> 00:01:35,480
I got the names of a few employers I would like to work for.
我找到了几个我想为之工作的雇主名字。

33
00:01:35,480 --> 00:01:39,720
I have the resume I wrote for English class last month and a cover letter will be a piece
我有上个月为英语课写的简历，写求职信对我来说是小菜一碟。

34
00:01:39,720 --> 00:01:41,200
of cake to write.
写起来。

35
00:01:41,200 --> 00:01:45,760
I've even done my research and found the names of the managers so I can address the letters
我甚至做了调查，找到了经理的名字，这样我就可以在信上

36
00:01:45,760 --> 00:01:46,760
personally.
直接称呼他们。

37
00:01:46,760 --> 00:01:49,640
And you know, I can be charming in interviews.
而且你知道，我在面试中可以很有魅力。

38
00:01:49,640 --> 00:01:53,640
Goodbye my penniless days, hello salary and a career.
再见了我穷困的日子，你好薪水和事业。

39
00:01:53,640 --> 00:01:55,560
Ben, we're 15.
本，我们才15岁。

40
00:01:55,560 --> 00:01:57,600
What kind of job are you looking for?
你在找什么样的工作？

41
00:01:57,600 --> 00:02:01,240
Oh, just for a position as a gas station attendant.
哦，只是应聘一个加油站服务员的工作。

42
00:02:01,240 --> 00:02:06,080
You know, starting at a simple lowly job just like all the greats before they made it big
你知道，从一份简单卑微的工作开始，就像所有那些成名前的大人物一样。

43
00:02:06,080 --> 00:02:07,080
in the world.
在这个世界上。

44
00:02:07,080 --> 00:02:08,400
Uh huh.
嗯哼。

45
00:02:08,400 --> 00:02:10,080
But I'm just in it for the money, right?
但我只是为了钱，对吧？

46
00:02:10,080 --> 00:02:13,920
How else am I going to be able to afford to keep taking Angela to the movies?
不然我怎么能负担得起继续带安吉拉去看电影呢？

47
00:02:13,920 --> 00:02:17,240
Besides, I love the smell of gasoline.
再说了，我喜欢汽油的味道。

48
00:02:17,240 --> 00:02:18,240
Don't you?
你不喜欢吗？

49
00:02:18,240 --> 00:02:19,760
Alright, we're back.
好了，我们回来了。

50
00:02:19,760 --> 00:02:25,400
So now you're probably wondering what those words meant.
所以现在你可能在想那些词是什么意思。

51
00:02:25,400 --> 00:02:31,480
So why don't we take a look at a couple of them in Language Takeaway.
那我们不如在“语言要点”环节看看其中几个。

52
00:02:31,480 --> 00:02:33,480
Language Takeaway.
语言要点。

53
00:02:33,480 --> 00:02:38,680
The first phrase we have today is one that's very important when you're looking for a job.
我们今天第一个短语在找工作时非常重要。

54
00:02:38,680 --> 00:02:41,840
It's called job listing or job listings here.
它叫做“职位列表”或“招聘列表”。

55
00:02:41,840 --> 00:02:43,840
Okay, job listings.
好的，职位列表。

56
00:02:43,840 --> 00:02:47,320
And this is really common before the internet existed.
这在互联网出现之前非常常见。

57
00:02:47,320 --> 00:02:50,480
You would have the listings in your local newspaper, right?
你会在当地报纸上看到这些列表，对吧？

58
00:02:50,480 --> 00:02:51,480
Exactly.
没错。

59
00:02:51,480 --> 00:02:56,320
In the movies, you always had the person sitting with the newspaper circling the potential
在电影里，你总能看到有人拿着报纸圈出潜在的。

60
00:02:56,320 --> 00:02:57,320
jobs.
工作。

61
00:02:57,320 --> 00:02:58,320
Right, with a red marker.
对，用红色记号笔。

62
00:02:58,320 --> 00:02:59,320
Exactly.
没错。

63
00:02:59,320 --> 00:03:02,400
But now that we have the internet, you have lots of websites that have job listings.
但现在有了互联网，有很多网站提供职位列表。

64
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:07,080
And so a job listing is literally a list of jobs that are available.
所以职位列表就是一份可供选择的职位清单。

65
00:03:07,080 --> 00:03:08,080
Okay.
好的。

66
00:03:08,080 --> 00:03:09,560
So you look through the job listings.
你浏览职位列表。

67
00:03:09,560 --> 00:03:11,080
Maybe you found one that's interesting.
也许你找到了一个感兴趣的。

68
00:03:11,080 --> 00:03:12,120
There's an email address.
上面有个邮箱地址。

69
00:03:12,120 --> 00:03:13,320
So what do they ask for?
那他们要你做什么？

70
00:03:13,320 --> 00:03:15,960
They ask you to send in your resume.
他们让你发送简历。

71
00:03:15,960 --> 00:03:16,960
Okay.
好的。

72
00:03:16,960 --> 00:03:20,520
A resume is very important when you're looking for a job.
找工作时，简历非常重要。

73
00:03:20,520 --> 00:03:22,160
It's a document.
这是一份文件。

74
00:03:22,160 --> 00:03:27,000
It's a piece of paper that tells someone all of the work that you've done before, your
它是一张纸，告诉别人你之前做过的工作、

75
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:31,800
job experiences, and it tells them where you went to school and what your qualifications
工作经历，还告诉他们你上过什么学校以及你的资格

76
00:03:31,800 --> 00:03:32,800
are.
是什么。

77
00:03:32,800 --> 00:03:34,840
So it's a summary of your work life.
所以它是你工作生涯的总结。

78
00:03:34,840 --> 00:03:35,840
Okay.
好的。

79
00:03:35,840 --> 00:03:37,160
And that's why it's called a resume, right?
这就是为什么它叫简历，对吧？

80
00:03:37,160 --> 00:03:40,360
It's pretty much a summary of your work life, as you say.
正如你所说，它基本上是你工作生涯的总结。

81
00:03:40,360 --> 00:03:41,360
That's right.
没错。

82
00:03:41,360 --> 00:03:46,240
And a different one, sometimes people use this, is a CV, curriculum vitae, and that's
另一种不同的说法，有时人们会用这个，就是 CV，curriculum vitae，那是

83
00:03:46,240 --> 00:03:48,860
an academic summary of your life.
你人生的学术总结。

84
00:03:48,860 --> 00:03:52,320
So you have the work summary and the study summary.
所以你有工作总结和学习总结。

85
00:03:52,320 --> 00:03:53,320
Okay.
好的。

86
00:03:53,320 --> 00:03:54,320
Very good.
非常好。

87
00:03:54,320 --> 00:03:59,080
So if you send in your resume, what's recommended is that you attach it with a cover letter.
所以如果你寄出简历，建议你附上一封求职信。

88
00:03:59,080 --> 00:04:00,080
Okay.
好的。

89
00:04:00,080 --> 00:04:02,320
Well, cover letter, you know the word letter.
嗯，求职信，你知道“信”这个词。

90
00:04:02,320 --> 00:04:04,680
It's something that you write to somebody else.
这是你写给别人的东西。

91
00:04:04,680 --> 00:04:07,840
But a cover letter is like a cover for your resume.
但求职信就像是你简历的封面。

92
00:04:07,840 --> 00:04:14,480
It's a letter where you explain to the future boss or future employer what exactly you want
这是一封信，你在信中向未来的老板或未来雇主解释你到底想要什么，

93
00:04:14,480 --> 00:04:17,400
and how this job is going to help you get it.
以及这份工作如何帮助你实现它。

94
00:04:17,400 --> 00:04:18,400
Okay.
好的。

95
00:04:18,400 --> 00:04:21,920
So that's basically a small little introduction to yourself, right?
所以这基本上是一个简短的个人介绍，对吧？

96
00:04:21,920 --> 00:04:26,440
Before they read your resume, who you are, what you're looking for, maybe very quickly.
在他们读你的简历之前，你是谁，你在找什么，可能非常简短。

97
00:04:26,440 --> 00:04:27,440
Exactly.
正是。

98
00:04:27,440 --> 00:04:29,120
So you can say, Hi, my name is Catherine.
所以你可以说，嗨，我叫凯瑟琳。

99
00:04:29,120 --> 00:04:33,840
I'm very motivated and excited to have the opportunity to talk to you about why I'm a
我非常有动力，也很兴奋有机会和你谈谈为什么我是一个

100
00:04:33,840 --> 00:04:37,720
skilled employee and why I will benefit your company.
有技能的员工，以及为什么我会让你的公司受益。

101
00:04:37,720 --> 00:04:38,720
Very good.
非常好。

102
00:04:38,720 --> 00:04:39,720
All right.
好的。

103
00:04:39,720 --> 00:04:41,800
So you've sent in your resume and your cover letter.
所以你已经寄出了你的简历和求职信。

104
00:04:41,800 --> 00:04:47,200
And well, maybe you're looking to get into a career as a gas station attendant.
嗯，也许你想进入加油站服务员这个职业。

105
00:04:47,200 --> 00:04:50,040
So what's the difference between job and career?
那么工作和职业有什么区别？

106
00:04:50,040 --> 00:04:51,040
Okay.
好的。

107
00:04:51,040 --> 00:04:56,320
And this is very interesting because in many languages, there is a similar word, which
这很有趣，因为在很多语言中，有一个类似的词，

108
00:04:56,320 --> 00:04:59,120
for example, in Spanish is carrera, right?
比如在西班牙语中是 carrera，对吧？

109
00:04:59,120 --> 00:05:01,880
And that means like a profession.
那意味着一种职业。

110
00:05:01,880 --> 00:05:05,920
So many people translate it literally as career, but it's not the right word.
所以很多人直译成 career，但这不是正确的词。

111
00:05:05,920 --> 00:05:07,720
What is a career?
什么是 career？

112
00:05:07,720 --> 00:05:12,040
A career I think of as a long term goal.
我认为 career 是一个长期目标。

113
00:05:12,040 --> 00:05:14,820
A career is your profession.
Career 是你的职业。

114
00:05:14,820 --> 00:05:16,240
It's the name you give yourself.
是你给自己的称号。

115
00:05:16,240 --> 00:05:21,000
But a job is a position in a company from one time to another.
但 job 是公司里从一段时间到另一段时间的一个职位。

116
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:26,000
So for example, my job here is host of EnglishPod.
所以例如，我的工作这里是 EnglishPod 的主持人。

117
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:29,400
But maybe in the future, I will have a media career.
但也许将来，我会有一个媒体 career。

118
00:05:29,400 --> 00:05:34,320
That means that my job or jobs will have to do with this profession.
这意味着我的工作或工作们将与这个职业有关。

119
00:05:34,320 --> 00:05:36,880
It's kind of a bigger thing, a longer thing.
这是一个更大的事情，更长久的事情。

120
00:05:36,880 --> 00:05:38,400
So maybe you can think of it this way.
所以也许你可以这样想。

121
00:05:38,400 --> 00:05:43,920
A career is like, as you say, bigger picture, like the macro category, right?
Career 就像，如你所说，更大的画面，像宏观类别，对吧？

122
00:05:43,920 --> 00:05:47,000
You're into media and television, for example.
你从事媒体和电视，例如。

123
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:50,760
And your job specifically is a podcast host.
而你的具体工作是一个播客主持人。

124
00:05:50,760 --> 00:05:56,440
But in the future, maybe I want to have a different job in this career and move into
但将来，也许我想在这个 career 中有一个不同的工作，并进入

125
00:05:56,440 --> 00:05:58,900
production and be a TV producer.
制作领域，成为一名电视制片人。

126
00:05:58,900 --> 00:06:01,080
So that's a part of my career path.
所以那是我 career 路径的一部分。

127
00:06:01,080 --> 00:06:03,120
I can move forward.
我可以向前发展。

128
00:06:03,120 --> 00:06:05,000
So career is very important word.
所以 career 是一个非常重要的词。

129
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:06,000
All right.
好的。

130
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:08,360
So we've taken a look at a couple of great words.
所以我们看了一些很棒的词。

131
00:06:08,360 --> 00:06:15,360
Why don't we listen to our dialogue again and we'll be back in a bit.
我们为什么不听一遍我们的对话，然后我们一会儿回来。

132
00:06:38,360 --> 00:06:42,480
I've even done my research and found the names of the managers so I can address the
我甚至做了研究，找到了经理们的名字，这样我就可以亲自

133
00:06:42,480 --> 00:06:43,480
letters personally.
写信给他们。

134
00:06:43,480 --> 00:06:46,720
And you know, I can be charming in interviews.
而且你知道，我在面试中可以很有魅力。

135
00:06:46,720 --> 00:06:48,600
Goodbye my penniless days.
再见，我穷困的日子。

136
00:06:48,600 --> 00:06:50,680
Hello salary and a career.
你好，薪水和 career。

137
00:06:50,680 --> 00:06:52,600
Ben, we're 15.
本，我们才15岁。

138
00:06:52,600 --> 00:06:54,560
What kind of job are you looking for?
你在找什么样的工作？

139
00:06:54,560 --> 00:06:58,280
Oh, just for a position as a gas station attendant.
哦，只是一个加油站服务员的职位。

140
00:06:58,280 --> 00:07:02,640
You know, starting at a simple lowly job, just like all the greats before they made
你知道，从一份简单卑微的工作开始，就像所有伟人在他们

141
00:07:02,640 --> 00:07:05,440
it big in the world.
在世界上成功之前一样。

142
00:07:05,440 --> 00:07:07,120
But I'm just in it for the money, right?
但我只是为了钱，对吧？

143
00:07:07,120 --> 00:07:11,040
How else am I going to be able to afford to keep taking Angela to the movies?
不然我怎么负担得起继续带安吉拉去看电影？

144
00:07:11,040 --> 00:07:14,280
Besides, I love the smell of gasoline.
而且，我喜欢汽油的味道。

145
00:07:14,280 --> 00:07:15,400
Don't you?
你不喜欢吗？

146
00:07:15,400 --> 00:07:16,920
All right.
好的。

147
00:07:16,920 --> 00:07:18,880
We're back.
我们回来了。

148
00:07:18,880 --> 00:07:23,000
So now we have lined up for you three key phrases that we found in this dialogue.
所以现在我们为你准备了我们在对话中找到的三个关键短语。

149
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:27,520
So let's take a look at those now in Fluency Builder.
让我们现在在 Fluency Builder 中看看它们。

150
00:07:27,520 --> 00:07:29,080
Fluency Builder.
Fluency Builder。

151
00:07:29,080 --> 00:07:30,320
This first one's a great phrase.
第一个是一个很棒的短语。

152
00:07:30,320 --> 00:07:33,840
It's going to make you sound very fluent in English if you use it.
如果你用它，会让你听起来英语很流利。

153
00:07:33,840 --> 00:07:36,160
We say in the market for.
我们说 in the market for。

154
00:07:36,160 --> 00:07:38,160
I'm in the market for a new job.
我正在找一份新工作。

155
00:07:38,160 --> 00:07:39,160
All right.
好的。

156
00:07:39,160 --> 00:07:42,320
So this person is looking for a new job.
所以这个人在找一份新工作。

157
00:07:42,320 --> 00:07:44,480
He is in the market for.
他正在寻找。

158
00:07:44,480 --> 00:07:47,840
I could also say, I'm in the market for a new house.
我也可以说，我正在找一所新房子。

159
00:07:47,840 --> 00:07:51,120
Marco, do you know any good real estate agents?
马可，你认识好的房地产经纪人吗？

160
00:07:51,120 --> 00:07:55,080
So what does that mean if you say I'm in the market for a new job or you're in the market
所以如果你说我在找新工作或你在找，那是什么意思？

161
00:07:55,080 --> 00:07:56,200
for a new house?
是为了找新房子吗？

162
00:07:56,200 --> 00:08:00,040
I am right now actively looking for this thing.
我现在正在积极寻找这个东西。

163
00:08:00,040 --> 00:08:01,320
I really want one.
我真的很想要一个。

